[![PyPi Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/stonefish-license-manager.svg?style=flat-square)](https://pypi.org/project/stonefish-license-manager/)

<!-- [![PyPI pyversions](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/stonefish-license-manager.svg?style=flat-square)](https://pypi.org/project/stonefish-license-manager/) -->

The **S**tonefish **LI**cense **M**anager is a command-line tool and library
that manages your Python software licenses. Install with

```
pip install stonefish-license-manager
```

and install a new license with

<!--pytest.mark.skip-->

```sh
slim add <your-license-file-or-key>
```

All command line options are retrieved with

<!--pytest.mark.skipif(sys.version_info < (3, 11), reason="-h output changes slightly")-->

```sh
slim -h
```

<!--pytest-codeblocks: expected-output-ignore-whitespace-->

```
Usage: slim [-h] [--version]
           {list,ls,fingerprint,fp,info,i,add,a,remove,rm,clear-cache,cc} ...

Python license manager.

Options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --version, -v         display version information

Subcommands:
  {list,ls,fingerprint,fp,info,i,add,a,remove,rm,clear-cache,cc}
    list (ls)           List all installed licenses
    fingerprint (fp)    Display machine fingerprint
    info (i)            Show license info
    add (a)             Add license
    remove (rm)         Remove license
    clear-cache (cc)    Clear caches
```
